Women's 100 m - Athletics - Sydney 2000 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     The 100 m race was run in straight lanes on the homestretch in the Stadium. Athletes competed in preliminary heats, quarterfinals, semifinals and final. The best athletes from each heat (Q) and a number of "lucky losers" (q) advanced to the next level. Event facts: Women's 100 m competition was held at the Stadium Australia and 84 athletes participated in the event. 





These results for Women's 100 m - Sydney 2000 Summer Olympics - are based on the official olympic reports and the Olympian Database
